				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1143725">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I always have used CV to solo. I'm a bit lower than you, so I only have CV 1; my standard procedure is lead with Flame Spear from max range, and immediately hit Char, and start backing up - as soon as the mob is in range, hit them with Frostbite. From there, I spam CV until Frostbite wears off (generally 3 CV casts); there is time to get a FB in without breaking the CV chain. I'll usually refresh Char periodically too. I can solo 2-dots up to about 4 levels higher (after which the resist rate is too high), or 3-dots two levels higher (after which I run out of energy). Naturally, I apply the finishers whenever they trigger. If Frostbite is resisted, and it's not too dangerous a mob, I'll just spam CV until it's dead, but the tougher ones, I'll hit them with Freeze or Color Spray; it's rare that all three resist.<br />
<br />
This is at level 25.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
