				<div class="message">As an &quot;oldschool&quot; warrior i dont have much experience to playing Wizards.<br />
Decided to try something differnt with VG, and i'm really happy with Sorcerers.<br />
<br />
Since i solo single 4D a LOT (Euro on Deserted Flamehammer) i'm destined<br />
to try different things to improve my soloability. <br />
<br />
While it may not be the most efficient (read xp/min) solo method (AE = Best)<br />
i have &quot;found&quot; a viable way of using CV1/CV2 for Solo. Yes CV1/CV2<br />
<br />
For that you need to stack 2+1 things :<br />
- HP Regen / Qualian Armor<br />
- Critic Rating<br />
- CiS Robe (if you have)<br />
<br />
Its all in the &quot;Finishers&quot; and works great for killing &quot;Old Targonor mobs&quot; 46 4D with 60K+ xp per kill.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>You just use CV1/CV2 for main nuke to trigger the arcane finisher.</b><br />
<br />
<br />
Anyone else tried this route ?</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>sounds like a great way to maintain HP using the HP proc from qalian style and still ramp up cv damage.  add on a heal over time like shaman boon of borsid (like 60hp / tick) and you'd be golden.<br />
<br />
I've used a lower level CV to combine with mimic and fire finisher(s).<br />
<br />
Generally though with the new changes to flamespear, I can cast it at max range with a snared mob and it wont reach under that magical 25m range to get nuked on. follow it up with a char then clicky, back up a little re-snare and i'm gtg.
