					<div id="post_message_1151243">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I've been experimenting with CV2 and CV3 now at lvl 48 with FB3, and I have to say that cv2 is quite the spammable spell, <br />
<br />
With just one heal per fight I can spam it non stop on 3 dot mobs and never go oop, or stop at about 80% hp and use char/freeze/taq's to burn the rest down, and pull the next mob with minimal downtime.<br />
<br />
<br />
I was testing the differences out in the tehtamni temple area against the 3 dot birds lvl 47-48, chain pulled singles for about 15 min never ran oop, and g/f just tossed me a heal after each fight using cv2.<br />
<br />
When I swapped to cv4 the mobs would die maybe 10-12 seconds quicker, but I'd need at least 2-3 heals per fight, and also end them with much less power, around 85% each fight.<br />
<br />
Cv3 was a mix of the two, and took a lil more power than cv2 and i was close to the point where i'd need a heal to be safe so I wouldn't epic crit myself dead at the end of the fights, but it ended me in a deficit.<br />
<br />
so every 6-7 fights i'd need to use GE, and wait a few ticks for end regen to come back up.<br />
<br />
overall I think cv2 was the best option for singles and chain pulling, due to not running out of mana, and getting a quick heal after each fight.<br />
<br />
My g/f liked it more too as she got to nuke/dot the mobs much more as well without healing me so much.<br />
<br />
interesting thing is I notice more resists using cv2 against the same mobs vs cv4, I wonder if its just me tryig to make a pattern out of random, or if theres more behind it.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
